Load shedding will start at 1 pm this afternoon, Nelson Mandela Bay municipality spokesman Mthubanzi Mniki confirmed on Sunday. He said they were informed that the power utility will implement Stage 2 load shedding from 1 pm and this will likely continue until 10 pm. According to the alert sent out by Eskom there was a need to replenish and preserve emergency water and diesel resources to limit load shedding in the coming week.